      ## Testing a feature for the map

      The User Research team at trivago launched a pilot training for those interested in conducting their own user tests. The training included <em>writing a test plan, setting up a test on UserTesting.com, analysing the data and reporting the findings</em>.

      At the time I was also working on a feature for the trivago map, allowing users to see what places are nearby their hotel. Restaurants, shops, entertainment etc. So they can better plan their hotel stay.

      The name of this feature is called “What's nearby”. <em>So I used this training as an opportunity to assess the effectiveness of the copy</em>, as an entry point for adding places to the map.

