      ## Findings

      Whilst users understood that “What's nearby” was for adding places to the map. <em>Some participants thought they would only be shown near the <strong>selected</strong> hotel</em>.

      So we decided to change the copy to “Explore this area”. To make it clearer that <em>you’re searching for places within the visible map area</em>. Not just near the selected hotel.

